dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi lbw b Ganguly 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Ganguly takes out Afridi. It struck him just outside off stump, though. Afridi tried to paddle-sweep a length delivery coming in from just outside off, missed, and was hit on the pad. He was playing a shot and the point of impact was marginally outside off and was a tad unlucky to be given out lbw. That's Ganguly's 100th ODI wicket.

dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar b Umar Gul 97 (102b 16x4 0x6 149m) SR: 95.09

dismissalComment.html: Would you believe it? Tendulkar has got out in the 90's again. For the sixth time this year. It landed on a length, outside off stump and shaped away a touch, Tendulkar pushed at it, bat away from the body and at an angle, and got a fatal inside-edge. He stays there, resting on the bat, for a while before slowly turning to walk back.

commentTextItems.html: Dhoni has had enough of these singles and murders one over long-on to bring up the series victory. Dhoni walks across, shakes hand with Yuvraj, then collects one stump before shaking hands with Afridi who walks over to him. Jason chimes in: "It has taken 24 years for India to win a home series versus Pakistan." The last one was achieved on October 2 1983.

commentPostTextItems.html: It was Tendulkar's night at Gwalior. Exactly 18 years after making his debut on November 15, 1989, he lit up the arena with a stunning array of strokes and propelled India towards the series win. He drove, cut, whipped, walked down the track and moved outside leg stump and enjoyed himself in the middle. By the time he exited, for the sixth time this year on nineties, the game was sealed.
Malik: It [the loss] hurts but we are professional and we have to live with it.
Man of the Match Yeah, its him. Sachin Tendulkar.
"I think the most satisfying thing is we have won the match and the series. It [getting out in 90s] doesn't really matter. What matters and counts for me is winning for India.
"I thought that when the ball was coming on to the bat initially, it was important to stay there. We acheived it and I am glad to have contributed."
On Yuvraj and Dhoni: "They have played consistently in the series; today too they were very good.."

Dhoni: "It was a good team effort. The bowlers too bowled really well." They got a good start but in the end the bowlers bowled well, to the field." He praises Yuvraj for his contribution in the series and thanks the crowd for their support.
This is Sriram Veera, signing off. Thanks for logging on. Alvida!

dismissalText.commentary: Sachin Tendulkar b Umar Gul 97 (102b 16x4 0x6 149m) SR: 95.09

dismissalComment.html: Would you believe it? Tendulkar has got out in the 90's again. For the sixth time this year. It landed on a length, outside off stump and shaped away a touch, Tendulkar pushed at it, bat away from the body and at an angle, and got a fatal inside-edge. He stays there, resting on the bat, for a while before slowly turning to walk back.
